org.omancode.util.swing
Class LazyMutableTreeNode

java.lang.Object

      org.omancode.util.swing.LazyMutableTreeNode
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.tree.MutableTreeNode, javax.swing.tree.TreeNode
public abstract class LazyMutableTreeNode
extends javax.swing.tree.DefaultMutableTreeNode

A DefaultMutableTreeNode that lazily creates children when they are needed.

Creates children (via abstract method createChildren()) whenever getChildCount() is called. This can happen when the following are called:

  • DefaultTreeModel.nodeStructureChanged(javax.swing.tree.TreeNode)
  • DefaultMutableTreeNode.add(javax.swing.tree.MutableTreeNode)
  • JTree.expandPath(javax.swing.tree.TreePath)
The overall effect is that children are created as nodes are needed, i.e.: when expanded. In addition, more than what is expanded is loaded, particularly the children of the last unexpanded node at the currently expanded level of the hierarchy. Adapted from com.jidesoft.plaf.basic.LazyMutableTreeNode.
